# Code style

- Do not exceed 200 lines of code in any React component file. If it exceeds 200 lines, create a new component and import it.
- Do not use inline CSS styling. Use CSS files or shared tokens.
- Use a casual tone for any user-facing text. Do not use em dashes.

# Documentation

- When a new feature is added, add a short note under the Features section in `README.md`.

# React Component Structure

- Every React component must be created inside its own folder.
- Folder name must match the component name.
- Do not create standalone component files outside a component folder.

**Styles:** Each component must load its styles from a project CSS file (not inline). Prefer a colocated `Component.css` when the component has scoped rules. If it has no rules of its own, import a parent or shared stylesheet (for example `../RecipeForm.css` or `src/pages/shared/...`) and do not add a comment-only stub file.

Typical layout when the component defines its own classes:

```txt
Profile/
  Profile.tsx
  Profile.css
  index.ts
```
